   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# mosum.py: user guide\n",
    "\n",
    "## Installation\n",
    "`(.venv) $ pip install mosum`\n",
    "\n",
    "## Generating data\n",
    "We can simulate data from a mean-change model with `testdata`.\n",
    "The simulated data is stored in `x`, and the signal in `mu`."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "start_time": "2023-04-17T12:15:00.629539Z",
     "end_time": "2023-04-17T12:15:00.894193Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import mosum\n",
    "sim = mosum.testData(\"blocks\")\n",
    "x = sim[\"x\"]\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "pd.Series(x).plot()\n",
    "plt.plot(sim[\"mu\"], '-', lw=2)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## MOSUM procedure\n",
    "\n",
    "The function `mosum` uses a single bandwidth to detect changes.\n",
    "This returns an object with `plot`, `print`, and `summary` methods.\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ms = mosum.mosum(x, G = 20)\n",
    "ms.plot()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "start_time": "2023-04-17T12:15:00.886621Z",
     "end_time": "2023-04-17T12:15:01.171763Z"

    "## Multiscale MOSUM procedure with bottom-up merging\n",
    "\n",
    "The function `multiscale_bottomUp` runs the MOSUM procedure with multiple bandwidths, merging these from smallest to largest.\n",
    "Again, this returns an object with `plot`, `print`, and `summary` methods.\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%%capture --no-display\n",
    "ms_multi = mosum.multiscale_bottomUp(x, G = [10,20,40])\n",
    "ms_multi.plot()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],

    "## Multiscale MOSUM procedure with local pruning\n",
    "\n",
    "The function `multiscale_localPrune` runs the MOSUM procedure with local pruning, removing change point candidates locally to optimise an information criterion.\n",
    "Again, this returns an object with `plot`, `print`, and `summary` methods."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [

    "ms_multi_lp = mosum.multiscale_localPrune(x, G = [10,20,40])\n",
    "ms_multi_lp.plot()\n",
    "plt.show()"

    "# Confidence intervals\n",
    "To obtain confidence intervals, we can specify `do.confint = True` as an argument to the `mosum`, `multiscale_bottomUp` or `multiscale_localPrune` functions, or use the `confint` method for the resulting objects."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
